modules.description: Generates text sequences based on probabilistic state transitions derived from input data. It processes strings and lists of tokens, building transition tables to model sequence dependencies. Used to create pseudo-random text outputs resembling a given source's style.

Provides functions to build and manipulate a text generation state, including adding words, extracting sequences, and generating text based on a Markov model. Works with a custom generator type, strings, and hash tables to track word frequencies. Used to create coherent text sequences by feeding input and selecting next words based on statistical patterns.
